Pyllk---A Python implementation of the popular LianLianKan game.
LICENCE: GPL

Introduction
============
Pyllk is a game which I wrote in order to practise my Python and wxPython programming.

It is written in Python and uses the wxPython toolkit to build the GUI so it is cross-platform and can be run seamlessly on Linux, Windows(R), and possibly other platforms.
It implements the basic functions similar to that of llk_linux which was written in C and GTK+.

Installation
============
No installation needed.

Just run the pyllk.py file.
In Windows(R), double click on the file.
In Linux, run it in a terminal by typing ./pyllk.py or open it in a file manager such as Nautilus and choose RUN.

Requirements
============
Python(>=2.4) and wxPython(>=2.6) are needed to run the game.
	Python	www.python.org
	wxPython	www.wxpython.org

Reporting a BUG
============
If there is a bug or you have any question please Email me at pro711@gmail.com

